OL,3,CSafeguarding and costs concerns for
OL,4,Cnext year's Island Games
OL,6,FKaren Archenoul manager of Team
OL,7,FGuernsey said the Bailiwick's
OL,8,Fcompetitors have not 'bunked down' in
OL,9,Fdormitories for the games in over 20
OL,10,Fyears and while this may reduce
OL,11,Ffinancial outgoings it could bring
OL,12,Fother issues.
OL,14,FShe said: "I think times have changed.
OL,15,FChild protection issues and
OL,16,Fsafeguarding all come into play."
OL,18,FOrkney will begin to allocate
OL,19,Faccommodation from next week,
OL,20,Fprioritising athletes and officials.
